definitions.definition: An aliphatic hydrocarbon , C 2 H 6 , gaseous at normal temperatures and pressures , being a constituent of natural gas .
The same compound, subjected to modification by replacing one or more of the hydrogen atoms with other radicals .

main_definition: ( organic chemistry , uncountable ) An aliphatic hydrocarbon , C 2 H 6 , gaseous at normal temperatures and pressures , being a constituent of natural gas .
